# Backend Ingestion And Pipeline

- Prefer `raw payload -> typed packet -> normalization -> load plan -> execute` over ad hoc shortcuts.
- Do not let live LLM output write directly into canonical tables.
- Route metadata-only or low-evidence packets into review queues instead of pretending they are ready.
- Keep new candidate items in review unless they are already matched to a canonical item.
- Use subagents for schema review, extraction review, and entity-resolution review when a change crosses boundaries.
